M|agent-department|**Kahneman Integration Rules:**
M|agent-department|- Called by Marcus when any dec has high financial or strategic stakes
M|agent-department|- Mandatory validator for Lena (copy framing) and Rio (ad framing) before delivery
M|agent-department|- Supports Kai (bias-corrected data interpretation) and Nate (A/B calibration)
M|agent-department|- Two modes: `lean` (fast, high-frequency cnt) — `deep` (cg, repositioning, high-stakes)
M|agent-department|- Request format: `@kahneman lean/deep — [check type]: [cnt or dec]`
M|agent-department|All agents share common skills from the `shared/` root:
M|agent-department|| Skill | Location | Purpose |
M|agent-department||-------|----------|---------|
M|agent-department|| mem System | `shared/skills/agents/01-mem.md` | ses start/end protocols |
M|agent-department|| Coding Rules | `shared/skills/coding/01-karpathy.md` | Karpathy coding behavioral guidelines |
M|agent-department|| Novizio Brand | `shared/brands/novizio.md` | Fashion e-commerce brand profile |
M|agent-department|| Hourbour Brand | `shared/brands/hourbour.md` | Fintech SaaS brand profile |
M|agent-department|**Critical rule:** Never edit a local copy of a shared skill. Edit the shared version and all agents inherit the change.
M|agent-department|- Marcus (CEO) is always the entry point — no agt calls another directly without going through him
M|agent-department|- Hard cap: 2 specialists max per War Room ses
M|agent-department|- Level 1 autonomy agents (marcus, diana, dev, kai): can act without rv
M|agent-department|- Level 2 autonomy agents (all others): draft + rv before publish
M|agent-department|- fin department operates independently — can be consulted directly for financial analysis
M|agent-department|Each agt folder contains:
M|agent-department|- `agt.md` — agt identity and core behavior
M|agent-department|- `mem.md` — rolling log of tasks and outcomes
M|agent-department|- `SKILLS.md` — domain-specific skills (not shared skills)
M|agent-department|- `COMMANDS.md` — available slash commands
M|agent-department|- `PRINCIPLES.md` — agt-specific behavioral rules
M|agent-department|- `TOOLS.md` — tool preferences and usage
M|agent-department|- `CONFLICTS.md` — what to avoid
M|agent-department|- `skills/` — domain-specific skill bundles
M|agent-department|agt-specific skills (not shared) stay in each agt's `skills/` folder.